The paper deals with mathematical models of Markov processes and their use in denotational-semantic viewpoints, which are topics typically covered in the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses uncertainty measures and their interaction with security, which are relevant to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of monadic type with hiding over some state is a topic covered in Programming Languages (cs.PL), and the paper also presents a prototype in Haskell. Finally, the paper discusses the issue of compositionality in statistical databases, which is a topic covered in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
